note as RelationshipCorrections
  <b>Relationship cardinalities corrected by LLM review</b>
  BloodUnit "1" -- "*" Actor → BloodUnit "1" -- "0..1" Actor
    Reason: A BloodUnit may optionally be associated with a single Actor (e.g., donor), but not necessarily many. One-to-many is too restrictive.
  BloodUnit "1" -- "1" Actor → BloodUnit "1" -- "0..1" Actor
    Reason: A BloodUnit should have an optional association with one Actor, not mandatory one-to-one. Current cardinality is too strict.
  Operation "*" -- "2" State → Operation "*" -- "1" State
    Reason: Cardinality '2' is non-standard; an Operation likely relates to a single State (e.g., current state). Changed to one.
  REQ_BBT_01 "*" --> "*" Interface → REQ_BBT_01  Interface
    Reason: REQ_BBT_01 is a requirement identifier, not a domain class. This relationship should not exist in a domain model.
  REQ_BBT_01 "*" --> "*" Resource → REQ_BBT_01  Resource
    Reason: REQ_BBT_01 is a requirement identifier, not a domain class. This relationship should not exist in a domain model.
  REQ_BBT_01 "1" --> "1" Actor → REQ_BBT_01  Actor
    Reason: REQ_BBT_01 is a requirement identifier, not a domain class. This relationship should not exist in a domain model.
  REQ_BBT_01 "1" --> "1" Permission → REQ_BBT_01  Permission
    Reason: REQ_BBT_01 is a requirement identifier, not a domain class. This relationship should not exist in a domain model.
  REQ_BBT_01 "1" --> "1" State → REQ_BBT_01  State
    Reason: REQ_BBT_01 is a requirement identifier, not a domain class. This relationship should not exist in a domain model.
end note

note as ArchitectureCorrections
  <b>Architecture mistakes corrected automatically</b>
  [wrong_inheritance] Clinical_Team, Inventory_Manager, and Quality_Assurance use association (--|>) instead of inheritance (--|>) to Actor.
    Fix applied: change_class_type
  [missing_relationship] TransfusionRequestData is not associated with Reservation; a reservation links a transfusion request to blood units.
    Fix applied: add_relation
  [misplaced_class] REQ_BBT_01 appears to be a placeholder or requirement artifact, not a domain class; it has no defined role or attributes.
    Fix applied: remove_relation
end note

